<h3 __id__="927" class="wp-block-heading">4. SeaWorld San Diego</h3>

**of 55**  |  **Location**: Mission Bay

<img __id__="933" alt="My daughter watches the Manta roller coaster hurl down a track at SeaWorld San Diego." class="" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='2800'%20height='2096'%3E%3Crect%20width='100%25'%20height='100%25'%20opacity='0'/%3E%3C/svg%3E"/><figcaption __id__="934" class="wp-element-caption">Tweens and teens love the SeaWorld San Diego roller coasters.</figcaption>

SeaWorld San Diego alone draws tourists from all over the world to my city. They come to enjoy up-close animal interactions, fun rides, animal shows, and educational experiences.


ea otters, moon jellies, and more. You can touch reef sharks and marvel at giant ones in the walk-through shark tank.


This park seems to satisfy all ages equally, so families with toddlers and teens (and all ages in between) go here.

<ul __id__="939" class="wp-block-list">
<li __id__="940">Rescue Jr. play area entertains young kids with mild rides and lots to climb on. </li>
<li __id__="941">The Manta roller coaster and Electric Eel roller coaster thrill tweens and teens. </li>
