<h3 __id__="977" class="wp-block-heading">5. Sesame Place San Diego </h3>

**of 55** | **Location**: Chula Vista

<img __id__="983" alt="Elmo and Cookie monster walk with two girls through Sesame Place San Diego." class="wp-image-82871" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='1620'%20height='1080'%3E%3Crect%20width='100%25'%20height='100%25'%20opacity='0'/%3E%3C/svg%3E"/>

Sesame Place San Diego is the only theme park on the West Coast based entirely on **Sesame Stree**t. It replaced Aquatica San Diego water park. Here, you’ll find loads of water attractions and slides, seven themed dry rides, and an interactive musical play area.


The park also features an interactive **Sesame Street Neighborhood** complete with the iconic 123 Stoop, a live character show, a daily parade, photo opportunities, and everyone’s favorite characters.

<ul __id__="988" class="wp-block-list">
<li __id__="989">**What We Love**: It’s our biggest water park and a great way to cool off, especially in the inland heat.</li>
<li __id__="991">**Good to Know**: It’s open seasonally and a bit away from the main sights. </li>
<li __id__="993">**Tips**: It can get really hot here. To ensure you have shade, you may want to rent a shaded cabana or lounge chair.</li>
